An agent arrived (this session), read README + SKILL + all notes,
and still didn't know the branching workflow. The development
principles said 'dogfood' and 'test with real agents' but not
'use branches for features.' The agent worked directly on main,
overwrote the root tree constraint, wrote notes to the wrong ref.

Fix: principle 8 added to root tree constraint. But the deeper
issue is that SKILL.md is for any repo — it teaches the convention.
The development workflow is specific to THIS repo and lives in the
notes. An agent needs to read both the skill AND the project's own
notes to know how to work here. That two-step onboarding isn't
obvious unless someone tells you.
